oopener nofollow\">A2 Hosting</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/a2-hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"523\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/a2-hosting.png\" alt=\"A2 Hosting best WordPress hosting features\" class=\"wp-image-35533\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/a2-hosting.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/a2-hosting-300x215.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/a2-hosting-600x430.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>A bonus WordPress hosting service is<a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/a2-hosting/\"> A2 Hosting</a>. It’s a popular host known for its blazing-fast, reliable functionalities and technical support. They’re a developer-friendly web hosting company with all the flexibility and advanced features you need to create your WordPress site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On top of that, they offer free site migration, a free SSL certificate, automatic backups, and unlimited SSD storage. Like prior WordPress hosting services, A2 Hosting also comes with a cPanel dashboard, making it super easy to navigate and manage your hosting platform from your control panel.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Their expert support team is available 24/7/365 to help you get started and whenever you have an issue. A2 Hosting is an excellent choice for WordPress blogs and sites needing 99.9% uptime, top-notch support, and plenty of room to scale their website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A2 Hosting offers up to 20x faster servers than many competitors.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>A2 Hosting WordPress Hosting Company: Important Stats</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Speed</strong>: 285 ms</li><li><strong>Uptime</strong>: 99.9%</li><li><strong>Customer Support</strong>: 4/5</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>A2 Hosting WordPress Hosting Plans</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Shared Web Hosting: </strong>Starts at $2.99 per month</li><li><strong>Managed WordPress: </strong>Starts at $11.99 per month</li><li><strong>Managed VPS Hosting: </strong>Starts at $33.99 per month</li><li><strong>Managed Dedicated Hosting: </strong>Starts at $155.99 per month</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Each A2 Hosting plan has several sub-plans. These prices reflect a 36-month contract at the lowest cost for each.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-627198448ea4b wp-block-buttons\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-theme-background-color has-text-color has-background\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/a2-hosting/\" style=\"background-color:#009966\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">Get started with A2 Hosting </a></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2><strong>The Best WordPress Hosting Service Winner</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ve seen the best hosting for WordPress and what they have to offer, so now it’s time to decide which one is right for you.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ideally, if you want your hosting to help<a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-hacks-to-grow-your-traffic/\"> boost your SEO</a> and grow your business, you want to pick a fast service that promises over 99% uptime.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The best web hosting providers on this list are excellent, but our overall recommendation goes to SiteGround. As mentioned, SiteGround is one of the largest web hosting companies on the planet, and they are an official WooCommerce and WordPress recommended hosting provider.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Plus, SiteGround is affordable for WordPress blogs and small business websites. But, it can work for eCommerce sites as well. Best of all, you get terrific 24/7 support at any time.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-627198448eeea wp-block-buttons alignwide is-style-stacked\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button is-style-fill\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-theme-secondary-background-color has-background\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/siteground/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Get started with SiteGround</a></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"faqs\"><strong>Best WordPress Hosting Companies: FAQs</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some answers to frequently asked questions about WordPress hosting:</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>What Is WordPress Hosting?</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A WordPress host is where your website lives on the internet. You can think of WordPress hosting as a house where your website’s files, images, and content lives and are stored.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress hosting is web hosting designed for WordPress websites. For instance, WordPress<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-does-php-updates-by-your-web-host-impacts-your-wordpress-sites/\"> runs on PHP</a>. Good WordPress hosting platforms also run on PHP, meaning PHP upgrades are unlikely to cause any hassle.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In other words, it’s specially optimized to help your site load quickly and includes additional tools and functionalities to make it easy to manage your WordPress site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Do I Need WordPress Hosting to Start a Website?</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress.org is a free website platform, but you need a website hosting service to<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/guides/\"> build a WordPress website</a> unless you&#8217;re very tech-savvy. You don’t need to use one specifically for WordPress, but it’ll improve your site performance if you do.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>What Types of Web Hosting Services Are There?</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>There are <a href=\"https://www.techradar.com/web-hosting/what-are-the-different-types-of-web-hosting\">six basic types of web hosting services</a>: Shared Hosting, Virtual Private Server (VPS), Dedicated Server, Cloud Hosting, Managed Hosting, and Colocation. The type you should get depends on what functionalities your business needs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Note: </em></strong><em>Some web hosting companies use “shared hosting” and “managed hosting” somewhat interchangeably, so they may say “shared” when they actually mean “managed.” Be sure to read the fine print.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Below, you can learn a bit about the different types of WordPress hosting options available, including which (if any) of our favorites offer these plans. We’ve left out colocation because it’s just a rented space rather than a host in and of itself.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-627198448f3c0 wp-block-group is-style-decorated\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table alignfull is-style-stripes\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Type</strong></td><td><strong>Description</strong></td><td><strong>Best For</strong></td><td><strong>Offered By</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Shared WordPress Hosting</strong></td><td>Site shares servers with other sites using the same resources (RAM, CPU, etc.); often come with valuable tools</td><td>Startups with entry-level needs on a budget</td><td><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"A2 Hosting\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/a2-hosting/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">A2 Hosting</a><br><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Bluehost\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/bluehost/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">Bluehost </a><br><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"DreamHost\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/dreamhost/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">DreamHost</a><br><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"GreenGeeks\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/greengeeks/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">GreenGeeks</a><br><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"HostGator\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/hostgator/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">HostGator </a><br><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Hostinger\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/hostinger/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">Hostinger</a></td></tr><tr><td><strong>VPS Hosting</strong></td><td>In between shared and dedicated web hosting; sites get their own space on a shared server rather than sharing resources</td><td>Small business owners needing more control over their WordPress websites</td><td><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Bluehost VPS\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/bluehost-vps/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">Bluehost</a><br><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Dreamhost VPS\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/dreamhost-vps/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">DreamHost</a><br><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"GreenGeeks\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/greengeeks/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">GreenGeeks</a><br><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"HostGator VPS\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/hostgator-vps/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">HostGator</a><br><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Hostinger\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/hostinger/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">Hostinger</a></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Dedicated Servers</strong></td><td>Server rented by a single company sharing no resources; provide total control</td><td>High traffic businesses with tech experts</td><td><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"A2 Hosting\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/a2-hosting/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">A2 Hosting</a><br><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Bluehost\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/bluehost/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">Bluehost</a><br><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Dreamhost Dedicated Servers\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/dreamhost-dedicated-servers/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">DreamHost</a><br><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"GreenGeeks\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/greengeeks/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">GreenGeeks</a><br><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"HostGator\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/hostgator/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">HostGator</a><br>Hostinger<br><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"SiteGround Dedicated\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/siteground-dedicated/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">SiteGround</a></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Cloud Hosting</strong></td><td>Spread across several servers, limiting downtime; no building or maintaining infrastructure, several companies hosted on the cloud</td><td>Scalable with small business owners often paying only for what they need</td><td><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"HostGator\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/hostgator/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">HostGator</a><br><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Hostinger\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/hostinger/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">Hostinger</a><br>SiteGround</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Managed WordPress Hosting</strong></td><td>Nearly all aspects of managed WordPress hosting services are run by the web host, including setup, daily backups, management, operating systems, updating, etc.</td><td>Website beginners who are comfortable with handing over most site control in exchange for minimal work on their end</td><td>All of our favorites!</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>How Do I Choose the Best WordPress Hosting Site</strong>?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The best way to choose your WordPress site hosting service is to pay attention to these 4 factors:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li><strong>Speed:</strong> A web host server load time should be under 300 ms.</li><li><strong>Uptime:</strong> Any reliable WordPress hosting service has at least 99% availability.</li><li><strong>Customer Service:</strong> They should offer consistent help with WordPress hosting questions.</li><li><strong>Your Needs: </strong>The web hosting service should work with your business size and type. You should also consider if you have a team of beginners or advanced tech employees.</li></ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Any good WordPress hosting company prioritizes optimization so you can have a fast, user-friendly site that ranks higher in search engines and allows your business to grow.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On the other hand, a bad WordPress hosting company can lose visitors because they don’t want the hassle of slow load times, site downtime, and unreliable service.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more details, you can check out WPBeginner’s post on<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-hosting/\"> how to choose the best WordPress hosting</a> platform.</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2>Host Speed and Performance Test Methodology</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We used independent 3rd-party tools like Bitcatcha, Pingdom, and Load Impact to test the performance and reliability of each of these WordPress hosting companies, so the data above can help you make a reliable decision.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Below are a few speed and performance tests we ran on these best web hosting companies:</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. WordPress Hosting Service Load Times</h3>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"558\" height=\"218\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/wordpress-web-hosting-load-times.jpg\" alt=\"WordPress hosting service performance test by WPBeginner\" class=\"wp-image-35534\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/wordpress-web-hosting-load-times.jpg 558w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/wordpress-web-hosting-load-times-300x117.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>.We used Load Impact to analyze the performance of the web hosting server, primarily focusing on load time. Additionally, we gradually built up to 100 visitors at once because we wanted to see how the servers handle increased requests from multiple connections.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. WordPress Hosting Performance Speed</h3>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"558\" height=\"246\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/installing-wordpress-web-hosting-companies.jpg\" alt=\"WordPress hosting service speed test by WPBeginner\" class=\"wp-image-35535\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/installing-wordpress-web-hosting-companies.jpg 558w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/installing-wordpress-web-hosting-companies-300x132.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>We used Pingdom, an industry-leading website speed test service, to check speed across the WordPress hosting companies.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. WordPress Hosting Server Response Time</h3>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"558\" height=\"162\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/wordpress-hosting-plan-load-times.jpg\" alt=\"WordPress hosting service server response time test by WPBeginner\" class=\"wp-image-35538\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/wordpress-hosting-plan-load-times.jpg 558w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/wordpress-hosting-plan-load-times-300x87.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Bitcatcha helped us determine these web hosting providers’ server response times across geographical locations, including the US, London, Singapore, São Paulo, India, Sydney, and Japan.</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2><strong>Beyond the Best Hosting for WordPress</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this guide to the best WordPress hosting companies helped you find the right option for your hosting needs. Now that you know how to choose the top WordPress host, you should learn <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-best-practices/\">about WordPress website optimization</a> to drive more traffic and improve SEO rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To dig even further into running a WordPress site, check out these articles and tutorials:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-hacks-to-grow-your-traffic/\">30 SEO Hacks Guaranteed to Grow Your Traffic</a></li><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-cache-plugin/\">Best WordPress Cache Plugins</a></li><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-move-a-wordpress-site-to-a-new-domain/\">How to Move a WordPress Site to a New Domain</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s all for today! Don’t forget to follow us on social media and bookmark our site for more tips on search engine optimization, WordPress hosting services, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-hosting/\">7+ Best WordPress Hosting Services for 2022 (Compared & Tested)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-hosting/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:94:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"100 SEO Statistics to Help You Update Your Strategy for 2022\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:92:\"https://aioseo.com/seo-statistics/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=seo-statistics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:43:\"https://aioseo.com/seo-statistics/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 21 Apr 2022 12:00:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:8:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"SEO Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"100 seo statistics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"ecommerce seo statistics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"local seo stats\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"search engine marketing statistics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"seo statistics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:7;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"video seo stats\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=22425\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:334:\"<p>Are you looking for up to date SEO statistics? We decided to compile a mega-list of 100 SEO statistics to help you update your SEO strategy for 2021.</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-statistics/\">100 SEO Statistics to Help You Update Your Strategy for 2022</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49565:\"<p>Are you looking for up-to-date SEO statistics to help you map your strategy?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The world of search engine optimization (SEO) is complex and requires plenty of planning. <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/guides/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Creating a website</a> or small business means you have to think carefully about <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">your SEO strategy</a> if you want to see your brand thrive. Understanding key SEO statistics will help you make smart and thoughtful marketing decisions in the future.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We decided to compile a mega-list of 100 SEO statistics with the goal of helping you get a better handle on your SEO so that you can get more email subscribers, sales, and traffic.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Before we look at the stats, we&#8217;re going to answer a very important question: </p>\n\n\n\n<p>“What is SEO?” </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once we define the term, we’ll go over stats across various industries and platforms to get a better understanding of SEO and its impact on your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s get started!&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We want to help you navigate our compiled SEO statistics as quickly and efficiently as possible. Here’s a table of contents you can use to find the section that appeals to you.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"is-style-default\"><li><a href=\"#what-is-seo\">What is SEO?</a></li><li><a href=\"#google-ranking-factor-statistics\">Google Ranking Factor Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#local-seo-statistics\">Local SEO Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#ecommerce-and-small-business-seo-statistics\">eCommerce and Small Business SEO Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#video-seo-statistics\">Video SEO Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#voice-search-seo-statistics\">Voice Search SEO Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#mobile-seo-statistics\">Mobile SEO Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#search-engine-marketing-statistics\">Search Engine Marketing Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#off-page-seo-statistics\">Off-Page SEO Statistics</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"what-is-seo\">What Is SEO?&nbsp;</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"397\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/what-is-seo.png\" alt=\"What is seo? All in One SEO (AIOSEO)\" class=\"wp-image-22426\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/what-is-seo.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/what-is-seo-300x169.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/what-is-seo-704x396.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/what-is-seo-600x337.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>First, let&#8217;s explain what search engine optimization (SEO) is. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Essentially, SEO is the process of optimizing your site to rank high in search engines like Google so you can get more traffic to your site. The goal is to eventually make it to the first page of Google for your chosen keywords.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, but what do keywords really mean, you may think?</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-do-keyword-research-for-your-wordpress-blog/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Keywords </a>are ideas and topics that define what your site&#8217;s content is about. In terms of SEO, they&#8217;re the words and phrases that searchers enter into search engines. They can also be called &#8220;search queries.&#8221; You want the keywords on your page to be relevant to what people are searching for so they have a better chance of finding your content among the results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, making it to the elusive first page of Google means that more people will find your website, which opens the door to some pretty exciting marketing opportunities.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-best-practices/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">strengthen your SEO ranking</a> in many ways. Some businesses focus heavily on optimizing their website and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-sitemap-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Create a Sitemap in WordPress (The Easy Way)\">fine-tuning their XML sitemap</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Others spend their time creating blog content and building a consistent traffic source from platforms like Facebook and YouTube, which correlates with improved search engine rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In fact, high-quality content and link building are two of the most important ranking factors according to <a href=\"https://searchengineland.com/google-reveals-20-percent-queries-voice-queries-249917\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Search Engine Land</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The truth is, you need to consider all of this if you want to make your website accessible to a broad audience.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But that’s only the beginning.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>SEO is complex and can take some time to fully grasp, especially if you’re <a href=\"https://www.blogtyrant.com/start-a-new-blog/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">new to blogging</a> or running a small business. The journey to the front page of Google requires you to think carefully and use SEO statistics to make your content and marketing decisions.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that we’ve defined SEO, let’s move on to the statistics.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"google-ranking-factor-statistics\">Google Ranking Factor Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You can’t talk about SEO without bringing Google and ranking factors into the conversation. Google is the largest search engine in the world, and the most frequently visited website of all time. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, the number of Google searches increases every year.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"490\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-searches-per-year.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - Google searches per year\" class=\"wp-image-22427\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-searches-per-year.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-searches-per-year-300x208.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-searches-per-year-600x416.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /><figcaption>Image Source: <a href=\"https://www.internetlivestats.com/google-search-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Internet Live Stats</a></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Because of Google’s popularity, its ranking system for websites based on search relevance and performance is the standard used by virtually all business owners.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, Google uses over<a href=\"https://backlinko.com/google-ranking-factors#pagelevel\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\"> 200 factors</a> in its algorithm for ranking websites. These <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/seo-ranking-factors/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">SEO ranking factors</a> include domain age, keywords, mobile friendliness, number of internal links, and much more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out some more interesting Google ranking factor stats:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Out of all of the website traffic in the world, <a href=\"https://www.statista.com/statistics/216573/worldwide-market-share-of-search-engines/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">92.47%</a> goes through Google&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li><a href=\"https://videos.brightedge.com/research-report/BrightEdge_ChannelReport2019_FINAL.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">68%</a> of online experiences start with a search engine</li><li>Believe it or not, Google receives over <a href=\"https://www.internetlivestats.com/google-search-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">7.8 billion</a> searches every single day</li><li>Research shows that <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/insiders/inbound-marketing-stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">75%</a> of searchers don’t bother clicking past the results on the first page</li><li>The first 5 results for a given search account for <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/digital-marketing-statistics/#seostatistics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">67%</a> of all clicks</li><li>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://ahrefs.com/blog/search-traffic-study/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">91%</a> of all websites never receive organic traffic from Google due to not having backlinks</li><li><a href=\"https://www.slideshare.net/randfish/keepng-up-wth-seo-n-2017-beyond/11-Keyword_Length_of_Search_Queries1Word\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">54.31%</a> of search queries contain 3 or more words</li><li>The average person searches for something online <a href=\"https://ardorseo.com/blog/how-many-google-searches-per-day-2019/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">3-4 times</a> a day</li><li>Analysts predict that between <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/local-seo-stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">16% and 20%</a> of all user searches are brand new keywords and phrases, which should get you excited about optimizing your content for new keywords</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>According to <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/search-engine-ranking\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Backlinko</a> pages with shorter URLs are often given favor in search rankings, as well as sites with a lower bounce rate and faster loading times.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Check your loading times with <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/free-website-speed-test-tool-for-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">IsItWP’s FREE speed test</a> to see where you stand!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google is also using CTR (Click-Through-Rate) as a ranking factor. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, the more people you get to click through to your website, the better page rank you&#8217;ll get in search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"486\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/ctr-graph-by-aioseo.png\" alt=\"Average CTR per position in search results graph by AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-38865\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/ctr-graph-by-aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/ctr-graph-by-aioseo-300x208.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/ctr-graph-by-aioseo-600x417.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/ctr-graph-by-aioseo-86x60.png 86w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/ctr-graph-by-aioseo-130x90.png 130w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, <a href=\"https://www.searchenginejournal.com/google-algorithm-history/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Search Engine Journal</a> states that Google introduces thousands of changes to its search engine algorithm every year. With that said, if you want to win at SEO, you have to play by Google’s rules.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"local-seo-statistics\">Local SEO Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>According to Google,<a href=\"https://www.socialmediatoday.com/news/12-local-seo-stats-every-business-owner-and-marketer-should-know-in-2019-i/549079/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\"> 46%</a> of all Google searches are local. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/a-complete-local-seo-checklist/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Local SEO</a> is a little different from traditional SEO. Instead of targeting a global audience, it’s all about reaching people who live in a specific place.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Business owners that have brick-and-mortar locations may take to the internet to promote their brand. Similarly, companies that offer a service like plumbing or electrical work use local SEO to reach their target audience.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll want to target keywords that use words that focus on location. If you have a sushi restaurant, you would want to use a keyword like “Sushi restaurants near me.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s also important that you list your business on Google so you can appear in the rankings. Include information about your company that new customers may need to know, such as your business hours, phone number, and address.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Including this information makes it easier for people to contact your company, which leads to more sales and visibility.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let’s continue with some interesting local SEO statistics.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"294\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-searches-statistics.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - mobile searches statistics \" class=\"wp-image-22430\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-searches-statistics.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-searches-statistics-300x125.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-searches-statistics-704x294.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-searches-statistics-600x250.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /><figcaption>Image Source: <a href=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/think/docs/think-with-google-2019-research-review.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Think with Google</a></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The terms “Where to buy” and “near me” increased<a href=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/think/docs/think-with-google-2019-research-review.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\"> 200%</a> over the past 2 years and search queries for “(store) near me” have grown <a href=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/think/docs/think-with-google-2019-research-review.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">250% </a>over the same 2 years. You might be surprised to learn that 28% of local business searches eventually turn into a sale.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Around one-third of all searches mention specific locations and 97% of people learn about local companies online more than anywhere else.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not to forget the growing number of mobile users. Did you know that <a href=\"https://www.thinkwithgoogle.com/advertising-channels/search/how-advertisers-can-extend-their-relevance-with-search-download/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">18%</a> of smartphone users made a same-day purchase after performing a local search? When asked, 54% of mobile users said they look up hours of local businesses, while <a href=\"https://www.thinkwithgoogle.com/advertising-channels/search/how-advertisers-can-extend-their-relevance-with-search-download/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">53% </a>looked up directions.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As a result, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/seo-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">56%</a> of local businesses that don’t have a listing on Google are losing out on potential customers. This statement is reinforced by the fact that 72% of people that use local search end up visiting a store within 5 miles.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>4 out of 5 consumers say they want more personalized offers that relate to their location, and about 70% of people said that businesses should put call and direction buttons in their ads.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>More importantly, allowing reviews for your local business can increase visibility and result in <a href=\"https://trustpulse.com/online-review-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">73%</a> more consumers trusting your brand.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On a final note, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-find-long-tail-keywords-and-increase-organic-traffic/\" title=\"How to Find Long Tail Keywords and Increase Organic Traffic\">long-tail keywords</a>, such as those used when coming up with local keywords, generate <a href=\"https://moz.com/beginners-guide-to-seo/keyword-research\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">70%</a> more traffic when compared to commonly used shorter words. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tips for Boosting Your Local SEO</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Want to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/a-complete-local-seo-checklist/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">boost your Local SEO</a> so you drive more foot traffic to your business?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are a few local SEO tips to get you started:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Optimize for local keywords</li><li>Creating a Google My Business account and completing your profile</li><li>Submit your site to local business directories</li><li>Getting more reviews from your happy customers</li><li>Writing content based on local news and events</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want more details on how to optimize your website, please check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">ultimate WordPress SEO guide</a> or <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/blog-post-seo-checklist/\" title=\"A Complete Blog Post SEO Checklist to Boost Rankings\">blog post SEO checklist</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"ecommerce-and-small-business-seo-statistics\">eCommerce and Small Business SEO Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We can’t have a list of SEO stats and not mention the importance of <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/ultimate-woocommerce-seo-guide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">SEO for eCommerce</a> and small business owners. Brands around the globe work on improving their SEO, so they can reach a broad audience that’s interested in their product or service.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Business owners and marketing teams have a ton of <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-woocommerce-seo-plugins/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">cool tools they can use</a> to boost their SERP (Search Engine Result Pages) position.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The general theme is that you want to get as many businesses and consumers as possible to find out about your brand through social media, email, and browsing Google.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s look at several small business and eCommerce SEO statistics you should keep in mind if you want to see your website make it to page 1 for your keywords.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"495\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/number-of-clicks-google-statistics.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - number of clicks on Google\" class=\"wp-image-22431\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/number-of-clicks-google-statistics.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/number-of-clicks-google-statistics-300x210.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/number-of-clicks-google-statistics-600x421.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /><figcaption>Image Source: <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/google-ctr-stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Backlinko</a></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>An impressive <a href=\"https://retail.emarketer.com/article/more-product-searches-start-on-amazon/5b92c0e0ebd40005bc4dc7ae\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">35%</a> of all product searches begin with Google, and on average, <a href=\"https://www.brightedge.com/resources/research-reports/content-optimization\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">40%</a> of revenue comes from organic visitors. This is the free traffic that’s the most desirable for businesses, as well as for consumers it seems since&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.blogtyrant.com/new-blogging-statistics/#engagement-stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">70-80% </a>tend to ignore paid content in favor of organic results.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In fact, leads from search engines have a 14.6% conversion rate, which beats out outbound marketing practices like cold calling by over 700%. Actually, <a href=\"https://www.brightedge.com/resources/research-reports/content-optimization\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">51%</a> of traffic from B2B and B2C sites comes from search engines.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know that businesses spend close to <a href=\"https://moz.com/rand/seo-consultant-agency-pricing-structure-services/#32\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">$5,000</a> every month on their SEO strategy, and will spend <a href=\"https://www.borrellassociates.com/industry-papers/papers/trends-in-digital-marketing-services-april-16-detail\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">$79.27 billion</a> on SEO by the end of the year?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On-page content, such as your blog, can increase traffic by as much as <a href=\"https://www.marketingsherpa.com/content_by_legacy_id?legacy_id=32133\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">2000%</a>, which can directly impact your SEO ranking. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Similarly, businesses that blog get <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/seo-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">524%</a> more pages indexed by Google, and <a href=\"https://neilpatel.com/blog/38-content-marketing-stats-that-every-marketer-needs-to-know/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">72%</a> of business owners and marketers claim that content creation is their number tool for improving SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Moving up 1 search engine results page (SERP) will boost your click-through rate by an average of <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/google-ctr-stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">30.8%</a>, which is fantastic. To be able to do this, it could be a good idea to pay extra attention to <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/search-engine-ranking\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Backlinko’s </a>research indicating that pages with at least one image, such as product pages, rank higher than businesses that only have descriptions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What is becoming more important for eCommerce businesses, is that the demand for same-day shipping is up <a href=\"https://www.thinkwithgoogle.com/marketing-resources/omnichannel/meeting-shoppers-needs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">120% </a>compared to 2015, and that trend seems consistent today. They better get their logistics on track so they can respond to this increased demand for same-day shipping.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tips for Boosting Your eCommerce SEO</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Boosting your eCommerce SEO is one of the best ways to generate inbound leads and increase sales. Here are a few ways you can ensure your eCommerce website performs well in search:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/10-quick-easy-ways-to-speed-up-your-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Optimize for speed</a></li><li>Make it easy to navigate through the different <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/posts-vs-pages-in-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">posts and pages</a></li><li>Create content that meets user intent</li><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-easily-find-and-fix-404-errors-in-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Fix any broken links</a> and optimize your 404 page</li><li>Design a strategic <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ways-link-assistant-can-save-you-time-on-internal-and-external-link-building/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">internal link building strategy</a></li><li>Proactively build backlinks to your pages</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, according to <a href=\"https://www.chatmeter.com/blog/growth-of-near-me-searches-shows-importance-of-local-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Chat Meter</a> responding to positive and negative feedback can help you improve your SEO ranking.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"video-seo-statistics\">Video SEO Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Optimizing videos for SEO is now an extremely common practice. The surge of mobile devices and the ability to show YouTube results on Google make this a strategy you don’t want to miss out on.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can optimize your videos by including transcripts, creating a catchy title, and by using a thumbnail that matches the content, just to name a few things. Like other areas of SEO, all of these small tweaks can lead to significant results.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s explore some video SEO stats so we can learn more about this brand-building technique.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"354\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/positive-return-on-investment-statistics.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - does video give you a positive return on investment \" class=\"wp-image-22432\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/positive-return-on-investment-statistics.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/positive-return-on-investment-statistics-300x150.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/positive-return-on-investment-statistics-704x354.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/positive-return-on-investment-statistics-600x301.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To make you understand the incredible power of video content, we want to start by sharing that YouTube users watch <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/video-marketing-statistics-what-you-must-know/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">1 billion</a> hours of content every day. And according to <a href=\"https://www.marketingcharts.com/digital/video-110520\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Marketing Charts</a>, it’s estimated that by 2021, the average person will watch 100 minutes of video content every day.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Imagine that!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>YouTube is the second-largest search engine in the world, with over <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/social-media-marketing-statistics/#YouTube-Social-Media-Marketing-Stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">1.9 billion</a> active monthly users, so this is a great source to tap into.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of <a href=\"https://www.renderforest.com/blog/video-marketing-statistics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Render Forest’s</a> surveys revealed that only 7 out of 10 marketers optimize their videos for search-ability, which is a bad judgment since <a href=\"https://chipthompson.com/19-fascinating-statistics-case-visual-content-marketing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">85%</a> of consumers in the United States only watch video content. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Imagine the whole world!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Although, <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/state-of-video-marketing-new-data\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">92%</a> of marketers say they plan on adding videos to their marketing strategy. They should really consider this based on the fact that <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/state-of-video-marketing-new-data\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">88% </a>of marketers say that video delivers a positive return on investment.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For instance, you’re 53% more likely to appear on the first page of Google if you add videos to your site, and you can also increase your organic SERP traffic by <a href=\"https://www.brightcove.com/en/blog/2015/08/create-compelling-video-experiences\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">157%</a>. That will surely lead to more conversions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The truth is that landing pages with videos get <a href=\"https://www.slideshare.net/AdelieStudios/adelie-studios-top16videomarketingstatistics2016-56658453\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">80%</a> more conversions. Including a video on your landing page also increases your chances of appearing on page 1 of Google by 53%.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Last but not least, we’ve already mentioned the importance of blog content. Blog posts with videos have a stunning <a href=\"https://www.convinceandconvert.com/content-marketing/year-of-video-marketing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">53x</a> greater chance of making it to the first page of Google, and adding videos to your blog posts can help you get <a href=\"https://moz.com/blog/what-makes-a-link-worthy-post-part-1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">3x</a> more inbound links.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tips for Boosting Your Video SEO</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Video SEO is slightly different from traditional SEO for written content. However, to boost your chances of ranking, here are a few factors:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Include a keyword-optimized transcript in the description</li><li>Include your focus keyword in the video title, video file, and metadata</li><li>Use relevant hashtags</li><li>Select the right video category</li><li>Create and optimize a <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/how-to-create-a-video-sitemap/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">video sitemap</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>With video fast becoming the most preferred content format, ranking your videos high on YouTube and other search engines has never been important. Use the video SEO stats and tips above to rank your videos high and drive traffic to your business.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"voice-search-seo-statistics\">Voice Search SEO Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Voice search is quickly becoming one of the most popular ways consumers find out about brands around the world. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Optimizing your website for voice search means understanding what a consumer will likely say, instead of type. Strangely enough, these two things are often different, and choosing the right keywords for voice optimization is crucial.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s now more convenient for people to simply talk into their phones or smart speakers instead of opening Google every time they have a question. Business owners and marketers realized that this trend was picking up early and got to work.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you haven’t started yet, don’t worry. It’s not too late to gear your site towards people using voice search.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But before you get started, here are some helpful voice search SEO statistics.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"261\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/voice-seo-statitics-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-22434\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/voice-seo-statitics-1.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/voice-seo-statitics-1-300x111.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/voice-seo-statitics-1-704x261.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/voice-seo-statitics-1-600x222.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /><figcaption>Image Source: <a href=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/think/docs/think-with-google-2019-research-review.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Think with Google</a></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The amazingly large number of 45 million people use voice assistants every single day, and Google Assistant usage has increased by <a href=\"https://www.thinkwithgoogle.com/data/google-assistant-user-stats/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">400%</a> in the last year.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.nationalpublicmedia.com/smart-audio-report/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Edison Research and NPR</a> mean that 1 in 6 Americans owns a smart speaker, making voice a common way to browse the internet, and&nbsp; 22% with smart speakers use their devices to buy products. This goes hand in hand with the fact that 40% of millennials use voice search to buy things online.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What is more, <a href=\"https://www.pwc.com/us/en/services/consulting/library/consumer-intelligence-series/voice-assistants.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">61% </a>of people between the ages of 25 and 64 claim that they plan on using their smart speaker for searching more in the future, and by 2022, it’s predicted that <a href=\"https://review42.com/resources/voice-search-stats/#:~:text=55%25%20of%20households%20in%20the,information%20about%20a%20local%20business.\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">55% </a>of households will have a smart speaker.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Almost <a href=\"https://www.seoclarity.net/next-generation-search-voice-17099/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">20% </a>of all voice searches are triggered by 1 word in a set of 25. The three most common trigger words include how, what, and best. Furthermore, the average word count of a voice search result page is 2,312 words.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And for all shopping lovers, did you know that Amazon and Google are responsible for <a href=\"https://www.strategyanalytics.com/strategy-analytics/news/strategy-analytics-press-releases/2018/01/02/loyalty-or-lock-in-most-smart-speaker-users-won%27t-budge-from-amazon-or-google\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">94%</a> of smart speakers used by consumers?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may also be surprised to learn that <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/seo-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">40.7%</a> of voice search responses come directly from <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/add-schema-markup-to-wordpress-without-a-plugin/\" title=\"How to Add Schema Markup to WordPress Without a Plugin\">featured snippets</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As mentioned earlier, turning your blog posts into video content can improve your organic traffic on that post by <a href=\"https://www.searchenginepeople.com/blog/8-blogging-stats-2017-strategy.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">157%</a>. According to <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/youtube-ranking-factors\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Backlinko</a> comments on your YouTube videos play a significant role in your ranking on search engines.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tips to Optimize for Voice Search</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Optimizing your site and content for voice search is easy if you know what to do. A few things to prioritize include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Create conversational content</li><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-faq-schema-in-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Include FAQ sections</a> on your posts</li><li>Optimize for local SEO</li><li>Optimize to rank for featured snippets</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>&nbsp;Voice search is here to stay. If can optimize for it you’ll succeed in tapping into an area of search that can drive conversion-ready leads.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"mobile-seo-statistics\">Mobile SEO Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"325\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-seo-statistics.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - digital around the world stats\" class=\"wp-image-22436\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-seo-statistics.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-seo-statistics-300x138.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-seo-statistics-704x325.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-seo-statistics-600x276.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Mobile SEO ties into many of the topics we’ve talked about today. Specifically, video and voice search have hit such a high level of success due to smartphone and tablet users.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you’re optimizing your site or social media for SEO, you have to think carefully about the experience you’re providing for your mobile users. Sites that are not mobile-friendly can’t get ranked on Google, so mobile readiness is a factor you need to consider.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don’t worry, we have your back. Here are some mobile SEO statistics that will help you get started:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://wearesocial.com/blog/2020/04/digital-around-the-world-in-april-2020\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">5.16 billion</a> people have mobile devices, and over <a href=\"https://www.statista.com/statistics/277125/share-of-website-traffic-coming-from-mobile-devices/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">51%</a> of internet traffic comes from smartphones and tablets</li><li>Google drives <a href=\"https://www.hubspot.com/marketing-statistics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">96%</a> of mobile traffic, and <a href=\"https://www.go-globe.hk/local-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">87%</a> of all mobile users interact with a search engine daily&nbsp;</li><li>The first organic search result for any given keyword gets <a href=\"https://www.seoclarity.net/mobile-desktop-ctr-study-11302/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">27.7%</a> of all clicks, and <a href=\"https://www.brightedge.com/resources/research-reports/mobile-first-57-traffic-now-mobile\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">79%</a> of all keywords show different Google results depending on whether a user is on desktop or mobile</li><li><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/seo-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">16.8 billion</a> smart speaker devices were shipped out by Amazon, Google, Apple, and other brands</li><li>Mobile voice searches are <a href=\"https://searchenginewatch.com/sew/opinion/2296905/how-will-voice-search-change-seo-for-local-stores-global-enterprises\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">3x</a> more likely to be based on a specific location</li><li><a href=\"https://www.thinkwithgoogle.com/marketing-resources/omnichannel/meeting-shoppers-needs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">60% </a>of smartphone users have bought a product that they discovered by using a search engine</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>We obviously like our smartphones. According to <a href=\"https://www.emarketer.com/content/mobile-time-spent-2018\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Emarketer</a>, most people spend 3 hours and 35 minutes on their smartphones every day.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, <a href=\"https://searchengineland.com/8-major-google-ranking-signals-2017-278450\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Search Engine Land</a> states that websites that aren’t mobile-friendly don’t rank on Google. Based on the fact that 61% of mobile users will contact a website if they discover a business website with a mobile-friendly layout it’s extremely important to ensure your site is mobile friendly.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tips for Boosting Your Mobile SEO</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ve seen the mobile SEO stats. They all point to one thing — you must optimize for mobile. Here are a few tips to help you do just that:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Build your site with mobile in mind (use a responsive theme)</li><li>Optimize for speed</li><li>Create a seamless experience between desktop and mobile</li><li>Optimize your content for mobile by using short sentences and paragraphs</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Failing to give users a <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/mobile-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">positive mobile experience</a> is unacceptable in this day and age. You stand to miss out on more than half the traffic on the internet.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"search-engine-marketing-statistics\">Search Engine Marketing Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Search engine marketing, also known as SEM, is an extremely popular marketing tactic that you can use for more growth. Simply put, SEM is a strategy where brands try to increase their visibility on search engines by using paid advertisements.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The goal is to get more people to click on your website, which will help you get more conversions and grow your lead list. We think that SEM is best used when combined with other areas of SEO, and experts agree.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Data from SEM campaigns can help you learn more about your target audience, which in turn opens the door for more optimization opportunities.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"410\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/paid-search-ads-statistics.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - top 4 reasons people click on paid search ads\" class=\"wp-image-22438\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/paid-search-ads-statistics.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/paid-search-ads-statistics-300x174.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/paid-search-ads-statistics-600x348.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s show you some stats that confirm this statement. For starters, the average company sees a <a href=\"https://www.powertraffick.com/google-ads-statistics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">200%</a> ROI with Google Ads, and <a href=\"https://databox.com/seo-vs-ppc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">86%</a> of experts use PPC (Pay Per Click) data to improve their SEO strategy. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is a smart move because stats show that if a consumer clicks a PPC advertisement, they are <a href=\"https://www.wordlead.com/facts/ppc-statistics-adwords-trends/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">50% </a>more likely to buy a product when compared to organic traffic. They have higher shopping intent.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As a matter of fact, one survey revealed that <a href=\"https://clutch.co/seo-firms/resources/search-engine-marketing-why-people-click-paid-search-ads\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">75%</a> of participants found paid search ads made finding what they were looking for easier, and 26% of people clicked on paid advertisements because they were familiar with the brand. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Additionally, 33% of respondents said they click on paid search ads because the promotional post answers their query.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not really surprising considering Google is the search giant, and in 2019, Google made over <a href=\"https://www.statista.com/statistics/266249/advertising-revenue-of-google/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">$134 billion</a> in profits from prioritized search ads. However, the spending on text ads went down <a href=\"https://www.merkleinc.com/thought-leadership/digital-marketing-report\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">14%</a>, but shopping on Google increased by 41% between 2018 and 2019.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google is probably not crying crocodile tears since its advertising and search tools helped the company bring a staggering <a href=\"https://comparecamp.com/sem-statistics/#TOC3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">$330 billion</a> to the U.S. market in 2018.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tips for Boosting Your SEM Results</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>While SEM leverages the pay-to-play system, it’s still a competitive marketing strategy. To ensure you get a good return on advertising spend (ROAS):</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Focus on keywords that meet search intent</li><li>Target your ads carefully</li><li>Don’t overlook negative keywords</li><li>Ensure your ads and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-optimize-seedprod-landing-pages-for-higher-rankings/\">landing pages</a> match</li><li>Always split test as much as possible</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Use tools like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site/\">Google Analytics</a> to track campaign performance to know what’s working and what needs tweaking.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"off-page-seo-statistics\">Off-Page SEO Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Off-page SEO is one of the most important aspects of growing your business. If other brands and websites aren’t linking to your company, and people aren’t sharing your posts on social media, you’re going to have a hard time ranking on Google.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Luckily, there are plenty of ways for you to improve your off-page SEO. We want to help you unravel the mystery once and for all by looking at some compelling off-page SEO stats.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"376\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/referring-domain-statistics.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - referring domain stats\" class=\"wp-image-22439\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/referring-domain-statistics.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/referring-domain-statistics-300x160.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/referring-domain-statistics-704x376.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/referring-domain-statistics-600x320.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /><figcaption>Image Source: <a href=\"https://ahrefs.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Ahrefs</a></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To start with, there’s a strong correlation between <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/social-media-and-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">social media popularity and SEO ranking</a> on Google. This is due to the fact that social media content is extremely shareable, so your site will get more traffic and visibility.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For instance, articles shared on social media see a <a href=\"https://blog.hootsuite.com/social-media-seo-experiment/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">22%</a> performance increase compared to those not shared. Google even crawls social media for relevant information. It’s no surprise that <a href=\"https://databox.com/social-media-and-seo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">91%</a> of marketers spend time optimizing their profiles for maximum exposure.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Better yet, websites with blogs tend to get <a href=\"https://www.stateofinbound.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">97%</a> more backlinks, which is one of the most <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/seo-ranking-factors/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">important factors for SEO</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Generally, the top result on page one for a popular keyword has nearly <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/search-engine-ranking\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">35,000 </a>backlinks. Building backlinks may seem like a walk in the park, but it’s not. In fact, <a href=\"https://www.smartinsights.com/digital-marketing-strategy/100-must-see-marketing-stats/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">65%</a> of marketers say that building backlinks is the most challenging aspect of SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And you soon realize the difficulty in building backlinks when studies show that&nbsp;<a href=\"https://ahrefs.com/blog/search-traffic-study/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">66.31%</a> of pages don’t have a single backlink. Further research shows that half of the businesses studied use <a href=\"https://comparecamp.com/sem-statistics/#TOC3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">25%</a> of their budget to build links. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The same research shows that 34% of companies spend an average of $1000 per month on their link building strategy. It adds up!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ahrefs stats show that the number 1 position for a given keyword gets 5-14% more backlinks from new business websites, and better yet, infographics generate <a href=\"https://www.quicksprout.com/content-marketing-lessons-learned/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">37.5%</a> more backlinks than traditional content.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tips for Boosting Your Off-page SEO</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>While of-page SEO takes place away from your website, you still have a hand in&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A few ways you can do just that include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Proactively <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/get-more-backlinks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">build backlinks</a></li><li>Have a strategic guest posting plan</li><li>Leverage social media marketing to drive traffic and boost social signals</li><li>Build a positive brand image and monitor your brand reputation</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Because off-page SEO works like third-party endorsements, search engines place a lot of value on it. That’s why you must invest in designing and deploying a robust off-page SEO strategy.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>SEO Statistics: Insightful Data to Benchmark Your SEO and Business Growth </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There you have it!&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ve now looked at over 100 SEO statistics that you can use to grow your business. You’re not going to see your business climb through the ranks overnight, but making it to page 1 of Google is entirely possible.&nbsp; </p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">SEO </a>is a lot like life, the more you put in, the more you’ll get out of it. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to see your site <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-do-an-seo-competitor-analysis/\" title=\"How to Do an SEO Competitor Analysis [The Easy Way]\">beat the competitors</a> and get tons of organic traffic, you have to put in the effort to optimize your brand for search optimization across all platforms.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thankfully, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</a> makes the SEO process easy!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO is the best WordPress SEO plugin, and it offers all the tools you&#8217;ll need to easily and efficiently optimize your site and improve search engine rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not using AIOSEO yet? What are you waiting for?</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-62719844986a1 wp-block-buttons\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button u-pl0\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-theme-background-color has-text-color has-background\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" style=\"background-color:#009966\" rel=\"\"><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-theme-background-color\">Get Started with AIOSEO Today!</mark></a></div>\n</div>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-statistics/\">100 SEO Statistics to Help You Update Your Strategy for 2022</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"https://aioseo.com/seo-statistics/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"4\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"Everything You Need to Know about Header Tags and How to Use them for SEO\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"https://aioseo.com/header-tags/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=header-tags\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://aioseo.com/header-tags/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 14 Apr 2022 13:12:47 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"SEO Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"header tags\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"heading tags\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"html headers\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=85290\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:434:\"<p>What are header tags, and how can you use them to boost your search engine optimization (SEO)? You’ve probably heard the terms header tags and how they help create optimized content.&#160; But what exactly are they, and how do you&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/header-tags/\">Everything You Need to Know about Header Tags and How to Use them for SEO</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16643:\"<p>What are header tags, and how can you use them to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">boost your search engine optimization</a> (SEO)?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ve probably heard the terms header tags and how they help create optimized content.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But what exactly are they, and how do you use them?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This post will clearly define header tags in a simple and easy-to-understand way. It will also show you the best practices for using them on your <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/posts-vs-pages-in-wordpress/\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><u>pages and posts</u></a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What are Header Tags?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Header tags, also known as HTML header tags or HTML heading tags, are HTML elements used to markup and separate headings and subheadings on a webpage. One of the most important functions of header tags is telling web browsers how to display content. Header tags rank in order of importance, starting from H1 (which is usually the title tag or most important heading) to H6 tags.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>A Quick Guide to Header Tags&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>How do you know which to use and when with so many header tags to use?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s a quick look at what each header tag means and where to use it in your content:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>H1</strong>: As said, an H1 tag is usually the title tag (page title) or headline of your blog post.</li><li><strong>H2</strong>: H2 tags are subheaders used to denote the main points of your paragraphs after the H1 heading. They also help separate distinct sections on a page.</li><li><strong>H3</strong>: You can use these for subsections that further clarify the points made in the H2. H3 tags work well for formatting lists under an H2.</li><li><strong>H4</strong>: H4 tags are used for subsections that clarify the points made in an H3. You can also use them to format lists under H3 tags.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The hierarchy continues with the H5 and H6 heading elements.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>6 Best Practices for Using Header Tags to Boost Your SEO</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know what header tags are, let’s dive into how you can use them to optimize your content for search engines and users.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. Optimize Header Tags with Keywords&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-seo-keyword-analysis-tool\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Keyword research</a> plays a central role in any SEO strategy. After all, you want to rank for particular search terms your target audience use.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One way to optimize your content is to include your keywords in as many header tags as possible. However, don’t be spammy with your use of keywords in header tags. Instead, be judicious and use them only when necessary. Otherwise, you’ll end up being penalized for keyword stuffing.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another tip for using keywords in your header tags is to frontload your keywords whenever possible.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Both will help you boost your on-page SEO, resulting in <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-best-practices/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">better chances of ranking</a> on search engine results pages (SERPs).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re an AIOSEO user, you can use our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-perform-website-seo-analysis-on-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">SEO analysis</a> at the bottom of the post to check if your page has a healthy number of keyword-optimized header tags.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"686\" height=\"322\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-keyword-optimization.png\" alt=\"Optimize your header tags for search by including keywords.\" class=\"wp-image-85317\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-keyword-optimization.png 686w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-keyword-optimization-300x141.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-keyword-optimization-600x282.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 686px) 100vw, 686px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>This will help boost the chances of your post ranking high in search.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. Use Header Tags to Reinforce Search Intent</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Header tags are a great way to reinforce that your content will meet search intent. While keywords are an important element of SEO, search intent is becoming equally critical. One of the first elements of your page that must show that your content meets search intent is your headline or page title. Your other header tags must also reinforce that your content does it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>How?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One way is to use Q&amp;A style header tags. This means asking questions in your header tags. Here’s an example:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"738\" height=\"478\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-user-intent.png\" alt=\"Using the Q&amp;A format in header tags helps reinforce search intent.\" class=\"wp-image-85304\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-user-intent.png 738w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-user-intent-300x194.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-user-intent-600x389.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 738px) 100vw, 738px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Using a Q&amp;A style format in your header tags helps users see at a glance that your content will answer the main questions they have.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another way to reinforce search intent is to use <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-find-long-tail-keywords-and-increase-organic-traffic/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">long-tail keywords</a> or their semantic variations in your header tags. The advantage of long-tail keywords is that they’re more descriptive.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When searchers see that your content will satisfy their intent, they’ll stay longer on our page. This signals to search engines that your content is valuable to users.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. Use Header Tags to Optimize Page Structure</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another use for header tags is to optimize your page structure. This helps users and search engine crawlers quickly grasp the context of your content. Used well, header tags help establish the flow of your content, improve information organization, and make it easy for users to scan your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using header tags this way helps improve user experience as it also helps break up your text as opposed to having walls of text. It also makes it easy for you to create a hyperlinked table of content for each piece of content you write. Additionally, using header tags to structure your content helps <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-improve-readability-score-on-wordpress-step-by-step/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">improve your readability score</a>. This is a metric that shows how easy it is for readers to read and digest your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can check your readability score under the <strong>Page Analysis</strong> in AIOSEO’s <strong>General</strong> SEO section.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"342\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-readability.png\" alt=\"Proper use of header tags can improve your page structure, resulting in better readability scores.\" class=\"wp-image-85305\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-readability.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-readability-300x147.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-readability-600x293.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<h3>4. Optimize Your Content to Rank for Featured Snippets</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Organizing your header tags well is an excellent way to optimize your content to rank for featured snippets. Google can pull items from your subheadings to create a bulleted or numbered list to show in the coveted featured snippets spot. Here’s an example:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"753\" height=\"418\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-featured-snippets.png\" alt=\"Header tags are a great way of optimizing for featured snippets.\" class=\"wp-image-85306\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-featured-snippets.png 753w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-featured-snippets-300x167.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-featured-snippets-600x333.png 600w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Google pulled the subheadings from the above post to create a numbered list, earning this site a featured snippet.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>5. Improve Accessibility</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To reach a wider audience, you should ensure that your website is accessible. Especially with <a href=\"https://web.dev/vitals/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Google’s Core Web Vitals</a> being a significant ranking factor, improving user experience must be a priority.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is where accessibility and the proper implementation of header tags come in.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Header tags help improve a webpage’s accessibility as screen readers can read HTML code. It helps visually impaired people determine whether the content on a page is worth reading. They also make navigation and scanning a page easier. Additionally, header tags can help provide shortcuts for visually impaired users to find particular sections faster. All these make for a positive user experience for visually impaired users.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>6. Be Descriptive</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Making your header tags descriptive is an excellent way of encouraging engagement. It makes your content lively, intriguing, and fun to read. As a result, time on page, an important SEO metric, is increased. Again, this signals to search engines that users love your content. This will lead to it being ranked higher in search.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Two Ways How to Add Header Tags in WordPress</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Headers tags play a crucial role in optimizing content for search and users. Therefore, knowing how to add them in WordPress is essential to creating content that ranks.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With all the talk of header tags being HTML elements, you’d think adding them in WordPress can be complicated, right?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not at all. All it takes is a few clicks of your mouse — no coding knowledge necessary. This is especially true if you’ve updated to the <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-use-the-new-wordpress-block-editor/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Gutenberg Editor</a> (WordPress Block Editor).&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. Adding a Header by Adding a New Block</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the easiest ways to add a header tag in Gutenberg is by adding a preconfigured block. To do this, first, click the Add (<strong>+</strong>) button and select the <strong>Heading</strong> option.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"744\" height=\"489\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-in-guternberg-adding-a-block-1.png\" alt=\"You can add a header tag to a post by clicking on the &quot;add&quot; button and selecting the &quot;Heading&quot; option.\" class=\"wp-image-85318\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-in-guternberg-adding-a-block-1.png 744w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-in-guternberg-adding-a-block-1-300x197.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-in-guternberg-adding-a-block-1-600x394.png 600w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Clicking on the <strong>Heading</strong> option will automatically add an H2 header tag to that block. To change the header tag level, click on the <strong>H2</strong> menu option, and select the tag type you want to add to that block.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"757\" height=\"314\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-in-guternberg-adding-a-block-2.png\" alt=\"Choose the header tag you want to add and click on it.\" class=\"wp-image-85319\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-in-guternberg-adding-a-block-2.png 757w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-in-guternberg-adding-a-block-2-300x124.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-in-guternberg-adding-a-block-2-600x249.png 600w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s it. You’ve added an HTML header tag to that block.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. Adding a Header Tag by Editing a Block</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you write your content in a word processor like Microsoft Word or Google Docs, you probably copy and paste your content into the block editor. Doing so will require you to add header tags by editing the necessary blocks. To add a header tag by editing a Gutenberg block, click on the block you want to add the header tag. Next, click on the <strong>Paragraph</strong> icon:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"702\" height=\"379\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-in-guternberg-1.png\" alt=\"You can also add header tags in WordPress by editing the paragraph type of the block.\" class=\"wp-image-85320\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-in-guternberg-1.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-in-guternberg-1-300x162.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-in-guternberg-1-600x324.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Clicking on the <strong>Heading</strong> option will automatically apply an H2 tag and open a menu where you can choose the header tag level you want to apply.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on the <strong>H2</strong> tab in the menu and you’ll be given a list of the header tags you can choose to apply to the block.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"702\" height=\"235\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-in-guternberg-2.png\" alt=\"Choose your header tag type and click on it to change the block\'s header tag markup.\" class=\"wp-image-85321\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-in-guternberg-2.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-in-guternberg-2-300x100.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/header-tags-in-guternberg-2-600x201.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Select the header tag you want to apply, and that’s it! </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Use Header Tags Strategically to Create User and SEO-friendly Content</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Header tags are an excellent way of ensuring that your content is created around <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-hacks-to-grow-your-traffic/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">SEO best practices</a>. But more importantly, they help organize your content in a way that’s easy to digest for readers. Doing so helps ensure that your <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/top-user-engagement-metrics-for-your-website/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">engagement metrics</a> improve. This results in search engines seeing your content as valuable to users, leading to better rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To better optimize your content, consider using a powerful SEO plugin like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">AIOSEO</a>. AIOSEO has impressive features that can help you easily boost your content and website by giving recommendations on:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/top-tips-for-good-on-page-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">On-page SEO</a></li><li>Off-page SEO</li><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-technical-seo-the-best-checklist-in-2022/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Technical SEO</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Even if you don’t have any technical or coding experience, you can DIY most of your SEO without needing professional assistance.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you haven’t downloaded AIOSEO yet, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">go ahead and get it here</a>.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/header-tags/\">Everything You Need to Know about Header Tags and How to Use them for SEO</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"https://aioseo.com/header-tags/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"What is Google E-A-T?  Understanding Google’s Secret Sauce for Creating Effective Content\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:100:\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-google-eat/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=what-is-google-eat\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-google-eat/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 12 Apr 2022 13:55:50 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"SEO Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Content Creation\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Google E.A.T\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=84851\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:449:\"<p>What is Google E-A-T, and how can it help you create content that ranks? The internet is a crowded place. With each day that passes, more websites are built, and more content is published. There are over seven million blog&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-google-eat/\">What is Google E-A-T?  Understanding Google’s Secret Sauce for Creating Effective Content</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13332:\"<p>What is Google E-A-T, and how can it help you create content that ranks?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The internet is a crowded place. With each day that passes, more websites are built, and more content is published. There are <a href=\"https://www.worldometers.info/blogs/\">over seven million blog posts</a> published every day to put it in context. Unfortunately, though, not all of them have valuable information for users.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is where Google E-A-T comes in.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What is Google E-A-T?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To ensure that users get the best experience, Google introduced E-A-T in their <a href=\"https://static.googleusercontent.com/media/guidelines.raterhub.com/en//searchqualityevaluatorguidelines.pdf\">Search Quality Evaluator Guidelines</a>. Google designed these to ensure the content published online is of high quality. E-A-T is an acronym that stands for:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Expertise</strong>: refers to the expertise of the creator of the main content.</li><li><strong>Authoritativeness</strong>: refers to the authoritativeness of the main content creator, the content, and the website the content is published on.</li><li><strong>Trustworthiness</strong>: Refers to the trustworthiness of the main content creator, the content itself, and the website it’s published on.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The purpose of these standards is to help improve the quality of content published on the web. In addition, it helps ensure that content is accurate and helpful to users.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Is E-A-T a Ranking Factor?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A frequently asked question about Google E-A-T is whether it contributes as a <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-best-practices/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ranking factor</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The simple answer is no.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, it goes deeper than that. Search engines like Google know that people can make life-changing decisions based on the content they find online. Therefore, the primary purpose of the E-A-T guidelines is to ensure the information search engines serve users is truthful, accurate, and helpful. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, there is a ripple effect that comes from publishing E-A-T-worthy content. One such effect is that it positively impacts your SEO, albeit indirectly. Here are a few ways in which E.A.T can do that:</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Helps Fight Disinformation</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Disinformation is a caveat that comes with free speech. In one of <a href=\"https://www.blog.google/documents/37/How_Google_Fights_Disinformation.pdf/\">Google’s publications</a> highlighting how they fight it, E-A-T is mentioned a lot. This just shows the important role it plays in ensuring that the information search engines serve users is accurate. Of course, this implies that content that meets the E-A-T standards stands a better chance of ranking.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Helps Improve Content Quality</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Content quality plays a massive role in boosting your SEO for many reasons. Some include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Increases the chances of your content being shared, thereby driving more traffic</li><li>Helps you get organic backlinks</li><li>Improves engagement metrics like click-through rates (CTR), dwell time, page views, and more</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Filler content that provides no value doesn’t cut it anymore. With many options available, people won&#8217;t waste any time on a website whose content isn’t helpful. Instead, they’ll quickly click away and find a better resource. Unfortunately, this results in high bounce rates, which indicate to search engines that your content doesn’t meet search intent.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Ensures Your Content Provides a Positive Experience</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Search engines are putting more emphasis on user experience (UX). Because of this, it must play a significant role in all your content creation and SEO efforts.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s another area in which Google E-A-T comes into play.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Applying Google’s recommendations for creating E-A-T content ensures publishers create content that offers a positive experience for readers.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>7 Ways to Create Content that Meets Google E-A-T Standards</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know what Google E-A-T is and why it’s important, let’s quickly dive into some elements to help you create content that meets Google’s E-A-T standards.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. Know Your Target Audience and What They’re Looking For</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the first ways to ensure that you’re creating E-A-T content is to know what your users are looking for when they input a search query. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Are they looking for information?</li><li>Do they want to buy a product now?</li><li>Are they checking out different products they want to buy soon?</li><li>Are they looking for a particular website/web page?</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The reason behind a search query is called search intent (or user intent).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Understanding search intent is pretty easy. A couple of ways to do it include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Use Google</strong>: Google your keyword and check the type of content that appears in the top results. This is what Google deems the most relevant answers for that search term.</li><li><strong>Use a Keyword research tool</strong>: Keyword research tools like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/semrush/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Semrush</a> show search intent as part of the keyword metrics.</li><li><strong>Check keyword modifiers</strong>: Using a keyword research tool, check the keyword modifiers used the most in other related keywords or variations of your keyword.&nbsp;</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve figured out what your audience is looking for, create content that answers their questions to the full.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. Create Data-rich Content</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another way to ensure that your content meets E-A-T requirements is to leverage data as much as possible. By citing facts and data from reputable sources, you show that your content is accurate. It also helps you showcase your expertise, make your content authoritative, and earns your readers&#8217; trust. Therefore data is the perfect ingredient for creating E-A-T content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides citing other resources, you can also conduct your own research. This has the advantage of establishing you as an authority and expert in your field. It also helps you build backlinks to your site, which brings us to the next point.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. Encourage Your Customers to Leave Reviews on Third-party Platforms</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Reviews are not just a powerful form of word-of-mouth marketing or social proof. They’re also a great way to build your website’s E-A-T, especially with <a href=\"https://developers.google.com/search/blog/2021/04/product-reviews-update\">Google’s reviews update</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"377\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-reviews.png\" alt=\"Reviews are an essential ingredient to meeting Google E.A.T standards.\" class=\"wp-image-84905\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-reviews.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-reviews-300x162.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-reviews-600x323.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<h3>4. Build Relevant Backlinks to Your Content</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Backlinks have been an important ranking factor since the inception of the internet. They’re also an essential element in creating E-A-T content. The main reason is that backlinks are a vote of confidence that your content is valuable and helpful. The more backlinks you build to a piece of content, the more authoritative it becomes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Note, however, that not all backlinks are created equal. You must build backlinks from high-authority sites relevant to your topic. Building backlinks from irrelevant backlinks will only signal to search engines that you’re simply building backlinks to game the system.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Reviews signal that users can trust you and that you&#8217;re an expert in your field. When your customers leave reviews (negative and positive), take time to respond to them. Doing so indicates that you’re reputable and committed to customer success.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>5. Include Author Bylines to Gain Trust</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One way to encourage trust in your content is by giving authors bylines. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"717\" height=\"422\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-author-bylines.png\" alt=\"Author bylines are an excellent way to boost your Google E.A.T score.\" class=\"wp-image-84906\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-author-bylines.png 717w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-author-bylines-300x177.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-author-bylines-600x353.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 717px) 100vw, 717px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Readers and search engines alike want to know who’s responsible for creating a piece of content and whether they’re a reputable source or not. To improve the author&#8217;s trustworthiness, you can also include links to their social media profiles or website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On the same note, try and involve subject matter experts as much as possible in your content creation process. This will ensure that your content is accurate and helpful. You can also leverage their credentials to boost your trust signals.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>6. Improve Security By Moving to HTTPS</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you haven’t yet, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/website-security/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">invest in your website’s security</a> by moving from the less secure HTTP protocol to the more secure HTTPS protocol. Doing this is another excellent way of proving that your site is trustworthy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To move to HTTPS, you must invest in a Secure Socket Layer (SSL) certificate. An SSL certificate is a digital certificate that authenticates a website’s identity. More importantly, it provides an encrypted connection protecting your visitors from malicious actors. Some great places for getting free or affordable SSL certificates include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/really-simple-ssl/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Really Simple SSL</a></li><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/namecheap/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Namecheap</a></li><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/domain-com-ssl/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Domain.com</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Ensuring that your website is secure is an important way of improving your E-A-T score.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>7. Make Your Contact Details Easy to Find</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another easy way to boost the trustworthiness of your website is openly displaying your contact details. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"287\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-contact-details.png\" alt=\"Including your contact details on your website is another way you can meet Google E.A.T standards.\" class=\"wp-image-85037\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-contact-details.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-contact-details-300x123.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-contact-details-600x246.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Particularly if you&#8217;re a location-based business, elements like your address and phone numbers signal to search engines and users that you are an entity users can trust.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>An added advantage of openly displaying your physical address is that it can also help <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/a-complete-local-seo-checklist/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">boost your local SEO</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Google E-A-T: The Blueprint for Content that Ranks and Converts</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Understanding Google’s search quality rater guidelines are essential to helping you create effective content. Following these guidelines will help ensure that your content is competitive in search.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Examples of such guidelines are the E-A-T  standards.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By following the tips above, you’ll be able to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-come-up-with-great-content-ideas/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">create content that ranks well</a>. But more importantly, your content will offer users a positive experience, resulting in better conversion rates.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For better chances of rambling your E-A-T content, consider using a powerful SEO toolkit like AIOSEO. AIOSEO is a WordPress plugin that makes it easy for non-techy people to optimize all three aspects of their sites — on-page SEO, off-page SEO, and technical SEO. If you haven’t downloaded this powerful plugin yet, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">go ahead and do so here</a>.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-google-eat/\">What is Google E-A-T?  Understanding Google’s Secret Sauce for Creating Effective Content</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:43:\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-google-eat/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"How to Optimize Your Landing Pages with the SeedProd &amp; AIOSEO Integration\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:180:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-optimize-seedprod-landing-pages-for-higher-rankings/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-optimize-seedprod-landing-pages-for-higher-rankings\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-optimize-seedprod-landing-pages-for-higher-rankings/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 08 Apr 2022 13:27:47 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"SEO Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"landing page optimization\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"landing page SEO\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"SeedProd SEO\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=84326\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:518:\"<p>Landing pages are specialized web pages that serve only one purpose — converting traffic into leads. A defining characteristic of landing pages is the form designed to capture visitor information.&#160; To ensure your landing pages succeed at converting traffic, they&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-optimize-seedprod-landing-pages-for-higher-rankings/\">How to Optimize Your Landing Pages with the SeedProd & AIOSEO Integration</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16462:\"<p>Landing pages are specialized web pages that serve only one purpose — converting traffic into leads. A defining characteristic of landing pages is the form designed to capture visitor information.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To ensure your landing pages succeed at converting traffic, they must be:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Designed to offer a positive user experience (UX)</li><li>Feature clear, crisp copy</li><li>Have one goal</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Because conversion is a priority, landing pages shouldn’t contain distracting elements or links to other websites. You must ensure the design and copy are optimized to funnel traffic to your offer.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Building Effective Landing Pages Starts with the Right Builder: SeedProd</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the first steps to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-checklist/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">building SEO-friendly landing pages</a> is to use the right landing page builder.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s why we recommend <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>SeedProd is the best WordPress plugin for building beautiful and effective landing pages for your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"347\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-homepage.png\" alt=\"SeedProd is a powerful yet lightweight landing page builder.\" class=\"wp-image-84329\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-homepage.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-homepage-300x149.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-homepage-600x297.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re wondering why, here are a few reasons SeedProd must be your landing page builder of choice:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Easy to use</strong>: Designed to be intuitive, you can easily build effective landing pages without any technical experience. This is all thanks to it being a drag-and-drop builder.</li><li><strong>Loads of pre-built templates</strong>: Whip up a landing page fast using SeedProd’s pre-built templates. All you have to do is fill in your copy.</li><li><strong>Easy to customize</strong>: The visual builder helps you see the changes you’re making to your landing page in real-time.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Ready-made content sections</strong>: With SeedProd, there’s no need to create every content section block by block. You can use the ready-made ones to speed up the process.</li><li><strong>Ready-made color palettes and fonts</strong>: Designed by experts, these make design work super easy, as you can pick one palette and have it applied to your entire page.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Whether you’re a beginner or advanced marketer, you’ll definitely love the powerful features SeedProd brings to the table. the ease of use that SeedProd affords</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>9 Best Practices for Building SEO-friendly Landing Pages with SeedProd</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Because of the high business value of landing pages, getting them to rank high must be every marketer’s priority. Thankfully, this is another area in which SeedProd shines. Let’s quickly dive into some of the best practices for building SEO-friendly pages with SeedProd.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. Leverage the AIOSEO/SeedProd Integration</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Nothing beats having an SEO plugin working from right within your page builder. It makes optimizing your landing pages so much easier as you can do it while creating them.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s exactly what you get if you’re an AIOSEO user.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you use SeedProd to build your landing pages and you’re an AIOSEO user, you can leverage AIOSEO’s SEO features within the page builder. To do that, you can click on <strong>Page Settings</strong> as you’re editing your landing page:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"198\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-aioseo.png\" alt=\"The SeedProd/AIOSEO integration makes optimizing landing pages easier.\" class=\"wp-image-84335\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-aioseo-300x85.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-aioseo-600x170.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>You can input your focus keyword and optimize your SEO title and meta description here. You can also implement schema and redirects if needed and other optimizations. These will help ensure your landing pages are primed to rank in search.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. Build Your Landing Pages Around the Right Keywords</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The basis of every SEO campaign is keyword research.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With landing pages, not every keyword is relevant. However, because conversion is the ultimate goal, you need to find:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Long-tail keywords</strong>: These have less competition and higher conversion value as they are more specific.</li><li><strong>Keywords with transactional intent</strong>: To increase the chances of ranking, driving traffic, and converting that traffic, your landing page must meet search intent.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>To help you uncover the best keywords for your landing page, use keyword research tools like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/ahrefs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Ahrefs</a>, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/semrush/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Semrush</a>, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/serpstat/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Serpstat</a>, etc. To improve your chances of conversion, build multiple pages per campaign, with each targeting a particular keyword.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. Craft an Optimized Landing Page Headline</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Headlines play a massive role in helping your landing page rank well and generate traffic. That’s why you must take your time crafting headlines optimized for search engines and appealing to users. A few tips to help you do that include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Frontload your keyword</strong>: Use your focus keyword and try as much as possible to put it at the beginning of the headline.</li><li><strong>Keep it short</strong>: Real estate on SERPs is limited, so keep your headline to within 60 characters.</li><li><strong>Make it descriptive</strong>: Despite being short, ensure that your headline is as descriptive of your offer as possible and try to highlight the primary benefit.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Both search engines and users consider headlines a primary indicator of what your content is all about. Your headline is one of your first chances of proving that your landing page will satisfy search intent.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>4. Structure Your Landing Page Well</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/top-tips-for-good-on-page-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">on-page SEO</a> technique you must never overlook on any page you create is page structure.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Content structure plays a considerable role in your landing page’s SEO. Make sure to structure your landing page so that it will be easy for search engines to understand what it’s about. More importantly, make it flow easily, so your visitors don’t struggle to digest the information. A few tips for optimizing your landing page’s structure include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Use lots of heading tags</li><li>Include images in your copy</li><li>Plan for white space</li><li>Use a simple, uncluttered template</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>A well-structured landing page makes it easier for search engines to understand the content and thus index it properly. This helps ensure that your landing page shows up for relevant search queries. It also improves your conversion rate.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>5. Optimize Your URLs</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>URLs play a crucial role in optimizing pages for visibility on search engines. That’s because a landing page URL helps communicate information about the content and purpose of your page to search engines. They also let users know that clicking on the link will take them to the answer they’re looking for.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another important reason for <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/top-tips-for-good-on-page-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">optimizing your URLs</a> is that they help search engines understand your site structure. This helps them crawl and index the page. A few ways you can optimize your URLs include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Keep them short</li><li>Include your focus keyword (frontloaded)</li><li>Be descriptive</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Customizing your URLs may look simple, but its impact on your landing page SEO is quite significant.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>6. Watch Your Page Load Speed</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another factor that plays a big role in landing page SEO is <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/10-quick-easy-ways-to-speed-up-your-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">page speed</a>. Especially with Google announcing that page experience is one of the major factors they use to rank websites, speed has become a priority for SEO. You can check how fast your landing page loads using tools like Google&#8217;s <a href=\"https://pagespeed.web.dev/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">PageSpeed Insights</a>, <a href=\"https://www.pingdom.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Pingdom</a>, etc.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"410\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-gtmetrix.png\" alt=\"Use a tool like GTMetrix to test your landing pages loading speed.\" class=\"wp-image-84336\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-gtmetrix.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-gtmetrix-300x176.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-gtmetrix-600x351.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Thankfully, this is one element SeedProd does exceptionally well. With SeedProd, you can be assured that your landing pages will be lightweight and super fast.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides using an optimized landing page builder like SeedProd, other ways you can ensure your landing pages load fast include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-image-compression-plugin/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Compress your images</a> or other media files</li><li>Minimize HTTP requests by keeping your landing page simple</li><li>Use a content delivery network (CDN)</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Slow loading speeds are detrimental to your SEO because it drastically increases your bounce rates. FYI, high bounce rates signal to search engines that users find a page irrelevant to the search term that brought them there. As a result, it’s demoted in rankings.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Fast pages, on the other hand, provide users with a positive experience, resulting in better rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>7. Optimize Your Metadata</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Before publishing your landing page, make sure you’ve optimized your metadata. This may not impact your rankings, but it helps convince users to click on your link in search results.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The two main types of metadata you should pay close attention to are the page title and meta description. To ensure yours are optimized, you must include your keyword close to the beginning of your keyword. Also, make sure they’re short, concise, and descriptive. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can easily optimize your landing page metadata using AIOSEO by heading to your <strong>Page Settings</strong> in SeedProd and clicking the <strong>SEO</strong> option.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"340\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-metadescription.png\" alt=\"Optimizing your metada in SeedProd is easy with AIOSEO built in.\" class=\"wp-image-84337\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-metadescription.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-metadescription-300x146.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-metadescription-600x291.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>You can then edit your metadata under the <strong>General</strong> tab.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>8. Optimize for Social Sharing</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>While search engines like Google say social engagement doesn’t directly impact rankings, you should still make your landing pages easy to share. One reason is that <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-integrate-social-media-into-your-website/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">social media</a> will help you drive traffic to your pages. The more people visit your pages, the more valuable search engines deem your pages to be.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sure, social engagement is not a direct ranking factor, but indirectly it helps boost your SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You must optimize the way your posts will look when users share your landing pages. Again, this is super easy to do with AIOSEO, especially when it’s nestled right within SeedProd. To optimize how your content will be represented when shared on social, go to your SeedProd settings and click on <strong>SEO</strong>. Then, in the <strong>General Settings</strong> section, click on <strong>Social</strong>. Doing so will open up a window where you can fill in all the necessary info to optimize for Facebook and Twitter.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"328\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-social.png\" alt=\"Optimize your landing page for social sharing using AIOSEO\'s social media markup.\" class=\"wp-image-84338\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-social.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-social-300x141.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seedprod-seo-social-600x281.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll also be given the option to choose where the image to be displayed should be pulled from.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>9. Build Links to Your Landing Pages</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Like all other pages on your website, <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/glossary/backlinks/\">building backlinks</a> to your landing page is a critical component of SEO. This is because backlinks are a vote of confidence that your page is relevant to search queries and offers valuable information. As a result, they are among the most significant ranking factors search engines use to determine how to rank pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A few tips for building backlinks to your landing page include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Check the sites linking to your competitors and ask them to link to yours. You can use tools like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/semrush/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Semrush</a> and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/ahrefs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Ahrefs</a> for this.</li><li>Encourage reviewers and those who write testimonials to link to your landing page.</li><li>Use brand mention tools to monitor unlinked mentions of your brand and ask the publisher to link to your landing page.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The more high-quality backlinks you build to your landing page, the higher it will rank. Therefore, you must carefully design and execute a link building campaign for each landing page you create.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Optimize Your SeedProd Landing Pages and Grow Your Business</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Landing pages are a crucial element of any digital marketing and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">SEO strategy</a>. Therefore, they must be treated with the utmost importance and be optimized for visibility and conversions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re an AIOSEO user, you can do both within your SeedProd landing page builder. So, go ahead and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">download AIOSEO now</a>.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-optimize-seedprod-landing-pages-for-higher-rankings/\">How to Optimize Your Landing Pages with the SeedProd & AIOSEO Integration</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-optimize-seedprod-landing-pages-for-higher-rankings/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"A Beginners Guide to WordPress REST API (and Its Impact on SEO)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:116:\"https://aioseo.com/wordpress-rest-api-and-seo/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=wordpress-rest-api-and-seo\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"https://aioseo.com/wordpress-rest-api-and-seo/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 05 Apr 2022 14:11:27 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"Headless WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"REST API\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"WordPress REST API\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=83789\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:407:\"<p>What is the WordPress REST API, and what does it have to do with SEO? The WordPress REST API has been a part of WordPress core since 2015. But it&#8217;s only in recent years that it has come into its&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wordpress-rest-api-and-seo/\">A Beginners Guide to WordPress REST API (and Its Impact on SEO)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7603:\"<p>What is the WordPress REST API, and what does it have to do with SEO?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The WordPress REST API has been a part of WordPress core since 2015. But it&#8217;s only in recent years that it has come into its own and became the next game-changer for WordPress websites. Sadly, however, this powerful WordPress feature has only been used by advanced users because of its complexity.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;ve <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-the-new-microsoft-clarity-integration-and-rest-api-addon/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">incorporated WordPress REST API into our plugin</a> to make it easier for beginners.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What is the WordPress REST API?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To better grasp the SEO possibilities of the WordPress REST API, let&#8217;s quickly look at it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>First, you need to know that the phrase &#8220;REST API&#8221; comes from two acronyms. Here&#8217;s what they stand for:</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>What is an API?</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>An application programming interface (API) is software that enables two applications to communicate with each other. APIs are very common and are used in many applications. For example, when you open Facebook on your phone, a request is sent to the Facebook servers, which is met by a response sent back to your phone. It&#8217;s more complicated than that. That&#8217;s the diluted version. However, the communication between Facebook and your phone is facilitated by APIs.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>What is REST?</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>REST stands for representational state transfer. It&#8217;s a standardized format designed to help web systems interface and communicate with each other. The five principles that govern this standardization include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li><strong>Uniform Interface</strong>: All application requests and responses must follow a standard protocol. This is usually the Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP) which is used to communicate over the internet.</li><li><strong>Client-Server</strong>: The host server and the application using the API (&#8220;client&#8221;) must be kept as separate systems. This allows them to be developed separately. Communication is facilitated when the client makes a request and the server responds.</li><li><strong>Stateless</strong>: All interactions with an API should be independent of each other. Each request and response must contain the required information to complete the exchange. As such, requests and references made are never referenced.</li><li><strong>Cacheable</strong>: All resources shared must be cacheable. When a client requests resources (data) from the server, the server must indicate whether said resources may be cached by the client and for how long. This helps improve speed and is in compliance with internet standards.</li><li><strong>Layered System</strong>: Clients and servers rarely connect directly over a network. Proxy servers are usually used to handle traffic, performance, and security. A RESTful system, therefore, allows you to use multiple layers. It also sorts out data in the proxy servers if needed.</li></ol>\n\n\n\n<p>These five principles standardize how web applications communicate. They ensure that all communication via the REST API follows the same processes. More importantly, they ensure that the two applications remain independent. Doing so ensures that a change in one application does not affect the communication between the two.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What Does REST API Mean for WordPress?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>For WordPress users, REST API opens up a host of possibilities. That&#8217;s because it enables other systems to interface with WordPress easily. The implications are that third-party websites or mobile apps can fetch and manipulate your WordPress data.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the most significant uses of REST API is that it allows developers to build websites powered by WordPress without building the frontend with it. In other words, they can harness the database, article drafting functionalities, and other features in the backend while developing the frontend of the website using a completely different framework.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is known as a <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/website/headless-wordpress\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">headless WordPress site</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>SEO: One of the Biggest Challenges Solved By WordPress REST API</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Headless WordPress gives you the ability to take advantage of the power of WordPress on the backend and use modern technologies on the frontend. While this makes for a powerful and beautiful website, there&#8217;s one major caveat — it complicates SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The main reason is that you can only implement most <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-best-practices/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">WordPress SEO practices </a>on the backend.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But with <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-the-new-microsoft-clarity-integration-and-rest-api-addon/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">AIOSEO&#8217;s REST API addon</a>, that is a problem of the past. This new addon plugin integrates with the WordPress REST API to support headless CMS installations. AIOSEO is a <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-seo-plugins-for-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">powerful WordPress SEO plugin</a> that helps non-techy users handle most SEO needs without hiring an expert. With the REST API addon, you can now manage your headless WordPress site&#8217;s SEO. To get started, head over to the <strong>Feature Manager</strong> section of the AIOSEO dashboard:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"412\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/rest-api-1.png\" alt=\"You can activate WordPress REST API in the Feature Manager section of your AIOSEO dashboard.\" class=\"wp-image-83794\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/rest-api-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/rest-api-1-300x177.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/rest-api-1-600x353.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Activate the REST API addon, and it will enable you to pull SEO data from the backend of your site and implement it on the frontend. This includes, among other things:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>SEO title</li><li>Meta description</li><li>Robots meta tag</li><li>Canonical URL</li><li>JSON Schema markup</li><li>Open Graph metadata&nbsp;</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>With the REST API addon active, you can fetch your SEO data via the WordPress REST API for any post or term. In addition, AIOSEO will automatically return all meta tags and values that it would normally output in the source so that you can implement them on the frontend of your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>WordPress REST API Addon: Giving You More Control Over Your Headless Site&#8217;s SEO</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO&#8217;s REST API addon is a game-changer for Headless WordPress SEO. Because it enables you to pull metadata from the backend of your website and implement it on the frontend, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-checklist/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">taking control of your SEO</a> becomes easier.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you haven&#8217;t downloaded AIOSEO yet, there&#8217;s no better time than now. So, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">get yourself the best WordPress SEO plugin</a> on the market.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wordpress-rest-api-and-seo/\">A Beginners Guide to WordPress REST API (and Its Impact on SEO)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"https://aioseo.com/wordpress-rest-api-and-seo/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:24:\"https://aioseo.com/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"\n	hourly	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"\n	1	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";O:42:\"Requests_Utility_CaseInsensitiveDictionary\":1:{s:7:\"\0*\0data\";a:17:{s:4:\"date\";s:29:\"Wed, 04 May 2022 10:16:05 GMT\";s:12:\"content-type\";s:34:\"application/rss+xml; charset=UTF-8\";s:13:\"last-modified\";s:29:\"Tue, 03 May 